This project contains a few scripts in python to analyzing heart activity data
files. Each script can be used alone or it can be imported as a module.

INPUT FILE FORMAT:
    The file should be built up with the three columns:
     - first column contains the total (accumulated) time of the recording (in
       minutes)
     - second column contains the RR interval (in milliseconds)
     - third column contains the annotation flag - 0 is for valid record and 1
       represents the invalid record 

FILES:
    validator.py
        Filtrate data, count number of lines of valid or invalid data.
    analyzer.py
        Calculate average, minimum, maximum, standard deviation of valid data
        stored in second column.
    plotter.py
        Plot 
        
COMMON OPTIONS:
    -f <file-name>, --file <file-name>
        Set input file. Default is standard input.
    -o <file-name>, --out <file-name>
        Set output file. Default is standard output.
    -h, --help
        Display help and exit.
    --filter <valid | invalid | all>
        Filtrate data before other operations.
        Default value is 'all'

OTHER OPTIONS:
    validator.py:
        -l, --lines
            Display number of lines of given data. Options -i, -v can change
            range of data which will be counted.
    analyzer.py
        --mean, --average
            Display average of second column.
        --min
            Display minimal value of second column.
        --max
            Display minimal value of second column.
        --std, --standard-deviation
            Display standard deviation of second column
        --all
            Display all information 
        -p, --pprint
            Display information in readable form with descriptions.
        --raw
            Display raw value. This option can't be used with option --all.
    plotter.py
        -T <delta-time>, --delta-time <delta-time>
            Set considering time interval to <delta-time> in minutes. 
        -n <n>
            Set which number of interval should be plotted. This option can't be
            used with options --min, --max, --mean, --average, --std,
            --standard-deviation, --histogram.
        --histogram
            Plot histogram of given range of data from second column.
        --bins
            Set number of equal-width bins in given interval.
        --min
            Plot minimal values for each interval <delta-time>
        --max
            Plot maximal values for each interval <delta-time>
        --mean, --average
            Plot average values for each interval <delta-time>
        --std, --standard-deviation
            Plot standard deviation values for each interval <delta-time>


    

         

